00:00:04,410 --> 00:00:06,870
CHAPTER ONE

2
00:00:06,870 --> 00:00:11,260
Cairo

3
00:00:11,260 --> 00:00:18,420
Monica noticed the gift shop, because of the
beautiful colours round its door and window.

4
00:00:18,420 --> 00:00:21,369
She walked through its entrance which had
a sign above it.

5
00:00:21,369 --> 00:00:28,040
On the sign, the word Cairo was written in
bright yellow, orange and green colours, with

6
00:00:28,040 --> 00:00:32,640
small black figures dancing beside it.

7
00:00:32,640 --> 00:00:37,700
Inside, it was just as colourful.

8
00:00:37,700 --> 00:00:43,000
Large animals made of paper, painted in very
bright colours, hung from the ceiling.

9
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:53,150
The floor had a yellow-brown sand colour to
it, and the shelves held vases, plates, boxes,

10
00:00:53,150 --> 00:00:57,570
musical instruments and jewellery Monica had
never seen before.

11
00:00:57,570 --> 00:01:04,860
No one seemed to be in the shop; not a salesperson
or a customer.

12
00:01:04,860 --> 00:01:11,010
Light Arab music came from a stereo Monica
could not see, but she moved with its sound

13
00:01:11,010 --> 00:01:16,020
as she looked at all the wonderful objects
in the shop.

14
00:01:16,020 --> 00:01:21,930
She saw a blue stone on a gold necklace which
looked interesting.

15
00:01:21,930 --> 00:01:27,840
Drawn in the centre of the stone there was
something which looked like a large round

16
00:01:27,840 --> 00:01:32,360
beetle, with thin legs and thick antennae
coming from its head.

17
00:01:32,360 --> 00:01:36,190
"It's an Egyptian scarab."

18
00:01:36,190 --> 00:01:41,280
The woman's voice surprised, then frightened
Monica.

19
00:01:41,280 --> 00:01:43,360
She almost dropped the necklace.

20
00:01:43,360 --> 00:01:47,560
"I'm sorry I didn't know anyone was here."

21
00:01:47,560 --> 00:01:48,960
"It's okay, my dear.

22
00:01:48,960 --> 00:01:53,410
I knew you would be here.

23
00:01:53,410 --> 00:01:54,410
Come.

24
00:01:54,410 --> 00:01:55,410
Come."

25
00:01:55,410 --> 00:02:00,700
The woman took Monica's arm and led her behind
the sales counter to a small area where there

26
00:02:00,700 --> 00:02:04,150
was a round table and two chairs.

27
00:02:04,150 --> 00:02:09,420
It was dark because cloth the colour of sand,
with dark patterns, hung from the walls and

28
00:02:09,420 --> 00:02:11,459
ceilings.

29
00:02:11,459 --> 00:02:16,970
It was almost closed off from the rest of
the shop by a curtain, so most of the light

30
00:02:16,970 --> 00:02:20,950
came from a few candles set around the room.

31
00:02:20,950 --> 00:02:24,860
It was like a small cave from somewhere far
away.

32
00:02:24,860 --> 00:02:25,860
"Sit.

33
00:02:25,860 --> 00:02:31,080
I've made us some tea, black tea; the tea
of judgement."

34
00:02:31,080 --> 00:02:32,080
"Judgement?"

35
00:02:32,080 --> 00:02:33,080
"Yes.

36
00:02:33,080 --> 00:02:38,450
The tea leaves tell us about a person's entire
life.

37
00:02:38,450 --> 00:02:41,470
Some of us have done things we wish we hadn't.

38
00:02:41,470 --> 00:02:44,380
Some of us haven't done things we wish we
had.

39
00:02:44,380 --> 00:02:45,380
Some of us are messengers.

40
00:02:45,380 --> 00:02:50,170
Some of us are waiting for the message."

41
00:02:50,170 --> 00:02:54,340
The woman wore a piece of red cloth tied around
her head.

42
00:02:54,340 --> 00:02:57,270
It hid the colour of her hair.

43
00:02:57,270 --> 00:03:00,900
Her eyes were large and dark.

44
00:03:00,900 --> 00:03:04,270
They became larger when she talked.

45
00:03:04,270 --> 00:03:10,460
As Monica sat at the table, she realised she
still had the necklace in her hand.

46
00:03:10,460 --> 00:03:13,130
"This stone is quite beautiful.

47
00:03:13,130 --> 00:03:15,680
I've never seen anything like it."

48
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:21,710
"It is lapis lazuli, the ancient blue stone
used to make statues for the gods.

49
00:03:21,710 --> 00:03:27,650
It was found in rock, and the rock had to
be burned and broken to get the lapis lazuli

50
00:03:27,650 --> 00:03:28,650
out.

51
00:03:28,650 --> 00:03:30,890
That shows you how strong it is."

52
00:03:30,890 --> 00:03:35,380
"Well, I'm sure it's too expensive for me..."

53
00:03:35,380 --> 00:03:40,650
As Monica was about to put the necklace on
the table, the woman closed her hand around

54
00:03:40,650 --> 00:03:42,850
Monica's, to keep the stone there.

55
00:03:42,850 --> 00:03:47,190
"Don't let it go, now that you have it.

56
00:03:47,190 --> 00:03:50,290
It may help you see things you never thought
were possible."

57
00:03:50,290 --> 00:03:51,290
"But...

58
00:03:51,290 --> 00:03:52,290
I..."

59
00:03:52,290 --> 00:03:57,959
The woman put her finger on Monica's lips
so that she couldn't talk.

60
00:03:57,959 --> 00:04:05,260
"Sit and listen and I will tell you the story
of the blue scarab."

61
00:04:05,260 --> 00:04:09,290
Monica held the necklace in her hand while
the woman spoke.

62
00:04:09,290 --> 00:04:15,480
Whether it was the heat of the room, the tea,
or the woman's soft voice, Monica began to

63
00:04:15,480 --> 00:04:18,799
fall asleep.

64
00:04:18,799 --> 00:04:26,721
"The scarab is the sacred beetle of the sun
god, the most important of all the gods as

65
00:04:26,721 --> 00:04:30,010
it makes people see things in a different
way.

66
00:04:30,010 --> 00:04:34,670
It is given to a different person every hundred
years.

67
00:04:34,670 --> 00:04:39,850
The person is chosen by the sun god to act
as a messenger for the dead.

68
00:04:39,850 --> 00:04:44,940
They see and understand things on earth that
help the gods decide whether the dead have

69
00:04:44,940 --> 00:04:48,870
lived good or bad lives.

70
00:04:48,870 --> 00:04:54,560
Those who wear it are sometimes frightened
because they are able to see the dead living

71
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:55,560
again.

72
00:04:55,560 --> 00:05:03,160
But they must keep the scarab, as the judgement
of so many depends on them."

73
00:05:03,160 --> 00:05:06,740
Monica heard the woman's words as she slept.

74
00:05:06,740 --> 00:05:12,590
She saw herself living thousands of years
ago, wearing the scarab.

75
00:05:12,590 --> 00:05:15,070
People were touching her hand as she passed
them.

76
00:05:15,070 --> 00:05:20,410
She was smiling and she felt very peaceful.

77
00:05:20,410 --> 00:05:24,389
When she opened her eyes, she looked at the
woman talking to her.

78
00:05:24,389 --> 00:05:28,120
"It looks good on you."

79
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:31,800
Monica touched the necklace with her fingers.

80
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:50,540
It was now round her neck.

81
00:05:50,540 --> 00:05:51,949
CHAPTER TWO
Herbie

82
00:05:51,949 --> 00:05:55,130
Monica's car had a broken headlight.

83
00:05:55,130 --> 00:06:03,070
As she drove to a garage to have it fixed,
the sun came down through the trees along

84
00:06:03,070 --> 00:06:06,389
the road, making everything seem more alive
than usual.

85
00:06:06,389 --> 00:06:11,990
There was an old man cleaning the ground in
front of the garage when Monica parked her

86
00:06:11,990 --> 00:06:12,990
car.

87
00:06:12,990 --> 00:06:16,800
He had his back to her, so she called to him:

88
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:17,800
"Excuse me.

89
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:19,380
Do you work here?"

90
00:06:19,380 --> 00:06:21,949
The man did not turn round.

91
00:06:21,949 --> 00:06:22,949
"Excuse me."

92
00:06:22,949 --> 00:06:25,850
Monica put her hand on the man's shoulder.

93
00:06:25,850 --> 00:06:29,479
He turned quickly and Monica saw her father's
face.

94
00:06:29,479 --> 00:06:32,450
Frightened, she put her hands over her mouth.

95
00:06:32,450 --> 00:06:37,050
Her father had died five years earlier when
she was eighteen.

96
00:06:37,050 --> 00:06:38,050
"Dad!

97
00:06:38,050 --> 00:06:39,050
Is that you?"â€ƒ

98
00:06:39,050 --> 00:06:41,610
Tears came to her eyes and her hands shook.

99
00:06:41,610 --> 00:06:54,430
The man moved his fingers to his mouth and
ears to show her he could not speak or hear.

100
00:06:54,430 --> 00:06:55,850
"Hello there!"

101
00:06:55,850 --> 00:07:03,060
It was the voice of a young man Monica knew
from the university.

102
00:07:03,060 --> 00:07:06,650
She had forgotten his name.

103
00:07:06,650 --> 00:07:08,810
"It's Owen, remember?

104
00:07:08,810 --> 00:07:13,920
We met at a party last winter."

105
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:16,680
"Oh, er yes!

106
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:18,530
I'm Monica."

107
00:07:18,530 --> 00:07:24,060
"I suppose you' ve met Herbie.

108
00:07:24,060 --> 00:07:33,860
He just started working here this morning."

109
00:07:33,860 --> 00:07:42,770
Monica wouldn't look at the man, afraid of
what she would see.

110
00:07:42,770 --> 00:07:45,920
He was talking to Owen in sign language.

111
00:07:45,920 --> 00:08:12,640
Owen spoke as he made the signs with his fingers.

112
00:08:12,640 --> 00:08:36,469
"Of course you can.

113
00:08:36,469 --> 00:09:53,910
I told you, Mr Burns lets us take our lunch
whenever we want.

114
00:09:53,910 --> 00:10:35,610
As long as you've finished your work.

115
00:10:35,610 --> 00:10:53,480
Okay, you're welcome."

116
00:10:53,480 --> 00:11:11,350
Herbie walked away.

117
00:11:11,350 --> 00:11:51,569
Suddenly, Owen noticed Monica's necklace.

118
00:11:51,569 --> 00:12:41,799
"Is that 

119
00:12:41,799 --> 00:12:52,329
a 

120
00:12:52,329 --> 00:12:54,509
blue scarab you're wearing?"

121
00:12:54,509 --> 00:12:57,189
"Yes, a woman at a shop gave it to me.

122
00:12:57,189 --> 00:12:59,050
She wouldn't take any money for it."

123
00:12:59,050 --> 00:13:04,029
"It was found in a chest believed to be the
chest of Osiris, an ancient Egyptian god.

124
00:13:04,029 --> 00:13:06,790
I read about it in my class on ancient Egypt.

125
00:13:06,790 --> 00:13:07,850
I study archaeology."

126
00:13:07,850 --> 00:13:10,589
"I think I saw you leaving that class once.

127
00:13:10,589 --> 00:13:13,240
I had an economics class right after it in
the same room."

128
00:13:13,240 --> 00:13:14,850
"It's a small world.

129
00:13:14,850 --> 00:13:16,739
So, what's wrong with your car?"

130
00:13:16,739 --> 00:13:18,069
"It needs a new headlight."

131
00:13:18,069 --> 00:13:19,069
"Oh, that's no problem.

132
00:13:19,069 --> 00:13:20,199
I can fix that in ten minutes.

133
00:13:20,199 --> 00:13:21,799
Why don't you go sit in the office?

134
00:13:21,799 --> 00:13:27,689
While you wait, Mr Burns will write out your
bill."

135
00:13:27,689 --> 00:13:33,639
In the office next to the garage, Mr Burns
sat behind his desk smoking a cigar.

136
00:13:33,639 --> 00:13:39,470
He was a short, bald man, but Monica didn't
know how short until he stood up to shake

137
00:13:39,470 --> 00:13:40,579
her hand.

138
00:13:40,579 --> 00:13:41,799
"Nathan Burns.

139
00:13:41,799 --> 00:13:43,589
Pleased to meet you."

140
00:13:43,589 --> 00:13:45,189
"Monica Halloway.

141
00:13:45,189 --> 00:13:46,370
Owen's fixing my headlight.

142
00:13:46,370 --> 00:13:48,629
Er, he said you'd write up the papers."

143
00:13:48,629 --> 00:13:49,970
"Certainly I will.

144
00:13:49,970 --> 00:13:51,019
You just have a seat there.

145
00:13:51,019 --> 00:13:54,819
I'll take care of it in two minutes."

146
00:13:54,819 --> 00:13:58,509
Monica looked out of the office window at
Owen working on her car.

147
00:13:58,509 --> 00:14:04,149
His thin, young face began to look old and
tired.

148
00:14:04,149 --> 00:14:10,439
It was as if she was looking at a completely
different man and it frightened her.

149
00:14:10,439 --> 00:14:12,930
Mr Burn's voice stopped her thinking.

150
00:14:12,930 --> 00:14:18,079
"How do you spell, Halloway, with two Ls or
one?"

151
00:14:18,079 --> 00:14:19,079
"What?

152
00:14:19,079 --> 00:14:20,079
Oh, two.

153
00:14:20,079 --> 00:14:25,050
H, A, double L, O, W, A, Y."

154
00:14:25,050 --> 00:14:29,819
Monica went outside to see Owen as he finished
his work on her car.

155
00:14:29,819 --> 00:14:34,300
He looked like he usually did, and Monica
forgot about what she thought she had seen

156
00:14:34,300 --> 00:14:35,300
before.

157
00:14:35,300 --> 00:14:37,149
She shook his hand.

158
00:14:37,149 --> 00:14:39,339
"Thank you very much for your help."

159
00:14:39,339 --> 00:14:40,339
"Anytime.

160
00:14:40,339 --> 00:14:42,480
It was nice to see you again."

161
00:14:42,480 --> 00:14:48,019
When Owen walked away, Monica saw Herbie sitting
on a chair by the garage door.

162
00:14:48,019 --> 00:14:50,329
He was eating a sandwich.

163
00:14:50,329 --> 00:14:51,939
She saw something on his right arm.

164
00:14:51,939 --> 00:14:57,009
It was a purple birthmark, the same kind her
father had.

165
00:14:57,009 --> 00:14:59,549
"It is you.

166
00:14:59,549 --> 00:15:02,109
I knew it!"

167
00:15:02,109 --> 00:15:05,939
She took a few steps towards Herbie, but she
frightened him.

168
00:15:05,939 --> 00:15:09,009
He got up and went into the garage.

169
00:15:09,009 --> 00:16:18,669
When she followed him inside, she saw that
he 

170
00:16:18,669 --> 00:16:28,869
had gone.

171
00:16:28,869 --> 00:16:58,910
CHAPTER THREE
Tops

172
00:16:58,910 --> 00:17:08,920
"Look.

173
00:17:08,920 --> 00:17:40,490
If you don't stop this, you'll get yourself
into trouble.

174
00:17:40,490 --> 00:17:41,640
It was a mistake.

175
00:17:41,640 --> 00:17:45,450
You saw something which wasn't there,"

176
00:17:45,450 --> 00:17:47,880
Yvonne was able to make Monica relax.

177
00:17:47,880 --> 00:17:51,880
They ordered their pizza and began to talk
about other things when

178
00:17:51,880 --> 00:17:54,560
Monica saw Owen across the room.

179
00:17:54,560 --> 00:17:58,060
"Now don't tell me I don't see him.

180
00:17:58,060 --> 00:18:01,690
That's the guy who fixed my car."

181
00:18:01,690 --> 00:18:05,880
Owen saw them looking over at him, and he
waved hello.

182
00:18:05,880 --> 00:18:07,550
He walked over and sat with them.

183
00:18:07,550 --> 00:18:09,980
"I'm glad I found you."

184
00:18:09,980 --> 00:18:11,420
"Owen, this is Yvonne."

185
00:18:11,420 --> 00:18:12,690
"Pleased to meet you.

186
00:18:12,690 --> 00:18:15,390
Look, I've read more about your blue scarab."

187
00:18:15,390 --> 00:18:17,450
"Wait a minute... wait a minute!

188
00:18:17,450 --> 00:18:21,200
I've just finished telling her that there
is no such thing as ghosts or sun gods or

189
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:24,180
whatever else you want to tell her."

190
00:18:24,180 --> 00:18:25,180
"Yvonne, let him finish."

191
00:18:25,180 --> 00:18:30,080
"The ancient Egyptians believed that Osiris,
the sun god's helper, used that stone so that

192
00:18:30,080 --> 00:18:32,550
people on earth could help those who had died.

193
00:18:32,550 --> 00:18:36,200
They thought dead people had to go through
a trial.

194
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:39,730
In that trial, they had to show that the good
things they had done on earth were greater

195
00:18:39,730 --> 00:18:41,580
than the bad things.

196
00:18:41,580 --> 00:18:44,850
Their actions could help the living improve
themselves by teaching them something.

197
00:18:44,850 --> 00:18:49,440
If the living learn something valuable from
the life of someone else, who is now dead,

198
00:18:49,440 --> 00:18:52,840
they can continue living their lives in a
better way.

199
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:55,910
This is good for the living but also for the
dead.

200
00:18:55,910 --> 00:18:59,880
The gods will see that the dead had lived
good lives since they continue influencing

201
00:18:59,880 --> 00:19:01,680
the living in a positive way."

202
00:19:01,680 --> 00:19:04,530
"Owen, that was thousands of years ago!"

203
00:19:04,530 --> 00:19:06,180
"Wait a minute, Yvonne.

204
00:19:06,180 --> 00:19:08,440
Let's just try to understand this.

205
00:19:08,440 --> 00:19:12,140
Do you think I could have seen a dead person
alive again?"

206
00:19:12,140 --> 00:19:16,390
"I don't know about that, but I know someone
who does, and he'd like to meet you.

207
00:19:16,390 --> 00:19:17,760
His name is Professor Lloyd.

208
00:19:17,760 --> 00:19:21,060
He taught that class on ancient Egypt I told
you about.

209
00:19:21,060 --> 00:19:22,910
Would you like to talk to him?"

210
00:19:22,910 --> 00:19:23,910
"Why not?"

211
00:19:23,910 --> 00:19:26,700
"This is mad!"

212
00:19:26,700 --> 00:19:32,390
Monica was silent for a few minutes, because
she was thinking of her father.

213
00:19:32,390 --> 00:19:34,320
She finally asked Owen about Herbie.

214
00:19:34,320 --> 00:19:38,170
"Who's that old man who is working at the
garage?

215
00:19:38,170 --> 00:19:39,990
What's his name, Herbie?"

216
00:19:39,990 --> 00:19:40,990
"Yeah, Herbie.

217
00:19:40,990 --> 00:19:44,190
Strange, but right after you left, we couldn't
find him.

218
00:19:44,190 --> 00:20:02,740
He never came back."

219
00:20:02,740 --> 00:20:16,660
CHAPTER FOUR
Professor Lloyd

220
00:20:16,660 --> 00:20:23,160
When Owen and Monica knocked on Professor
Lloyd's door, they heard a cat miaowing inside.

221
00:20:23,160 --> 00:20:29,820
They heard Professor Lloyd's footsteps coming
toward the door, then they saw him: a tall

222
00:20:29,820 --> 00:20:31,920
well-built man with glasses.

223
00:20:31,920 --> 00:20:37,490
He had straight, grey-white hair and a soft,
kind face.

224
00:20:37,490 --> 00:20:40,410
He welcomed them with a large smile.

225
00:20:40,410 --> 00:20:42,210
"You must be Monica."

226
00:20:42,210 --> 00:20:44,030
"Hello Professor Lloyd.

227
00:20:44,030 --> 00:20:45,400
It's a pleasure to meet you."

228
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:46,750
"The pleasure is mine.

229
00:20:46,750 --> 00:20:53,910
